## Spawn particles

```js
function spawnParticle() {
  if (particles.length >= config.streamMax) return;

  const source = nodes[Math.floor(Math.random() * nodes.length)];
  const angle = Math.random() * TAU;
  const speed = 0.3 + Math.random() * SQRT1_2;

  particles.push({
    x: source.x,
    y: source.y,
    vx: Math.cos(angle) * speed,
    vy: Math.sin(angle) * speed,
    age: 0,
    maxAge: 800 + Math.random() * 1200,
    size: 0.8 + (Math.random() * PHI) * SQRT1_2
  });
}
```

So a random node emits a little drifting particle.

---

## Update particles

```js
function updateParticles() {
  for (let i = particles.length - 1; i >= 0; i--) {
    const p = particles[i];

    p.age++;
    p.x += p.vx;
    p.y += p.vy;

    p.vx *= 1 - config.streamDecay * 0.125;
    p.vy *= 1 - config.streamDecay * 0.125;

    if (p.age > p.maxAge) {
      particles.splice(i, 1);
    }
  }
}
```

Particles slowly drift and slow down, then disappear.

---

## Update camera

```js
function updateCamera() {
  camera.x += (cameraTarget.x - camera.x) * config.theta;
  camera.y += (cameraTarget.y - camera.y) * config.theta;
  camera.zoom += (cameraTarget.zoom - camera.zoom) * config.theta;
}
```

This is smooth interpolation.

---

## Main tick

```js
function tickUpdate() {
  updatePhysics();
  updateParticles();
  updateCamera();

  if (tick % 3 === 0) {
    spawnParticle();
  }

  tick++;
}

setInterval(tickUpdate, 10);
```

That means:
- physics/particles/camera update every 10 ms
- particle spawns every 3 ticks = every 30 ms
- max 40 particles

